sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PatgF1GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: lac/IPTG inducible Spider Silk 1x "F" Subunit fused to GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a spider silk 1x "F" subunit with GFP fused to its C-terminus. This generator is lactose/ITPG inducible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brian Smith
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembly standard #23 assembly of basic parts

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spider Silk 1x Subunit "F" (Fewest tRNA codon optimized) with Met (ATG) added
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Spider silk subunit optimized to use the fewest number of tRNA codons; contains two elasticity domains and one strength domain, also contains 5??? Met (ATG) codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Charles Barentine
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Created using mutagenesis PCR to add upstream Met (ATG) to part BBa_K844003
